{
  "texts": [
    "These validation results are provided in Supplementary Fig. 4.",
    "The MLIP uncertainty is fairly constant and approximately equal to the AL energy threshold through nearly the entire simulation (with only a few snapshots as exceptions).",
    "The relatively low and constant uncertainty confirms that each system is well-modeled by our MLIP.",
    "It is also interesting that the MLIP uncertainty decreases with increasing O 2 /C 2 H 2 ratio, suggesting that ANI-1xnr is most confident under a higher O 2 /C 2 H 2 ratio.",
    "The reason for such a tendency is that more oxidation reactions happen in the system with a larger O 2 /C 2 H 2 ratio, which is a common reaction in our training dataset, although typically involving species other than acetylene."
  ]
}